{% extends 'base.html.twig' %}
{% set nav = 'communities' %}
{% block main_class %}{% endblock %}

{% block title %}Questions awaiting an answer: Sagamok Chief and Council · Robinson Huron Treaty{% endblock %}
{% block description %}A member-compiled, growing record of questions members have put to Sagamok Chief and Council that are still awaiting a reply, each tied to a public source or an as-filed document, with the date asked and the status.{% endblock %}
{% block og_description %}A growing record of member questions to Sagamok Chief and Council still awaiting a reply, with dates and status. Silence is its own answer.{% endblock %}
{% block body_class %}route-sagamok-awaiting-council{% endblock %}

{% block head_styles %}
<style>
  .awc{ --maxw:720px; color:var(--ink); font:18px/1.7 var(--sans); -webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased }
  .awc *{box-sizing:border-box}
  .awc .wrap{max-width:var(--maxw); margin:0 auto; padding:40px 22px 64px}
  .awc a{color:var(--accent); text-decoration:none}
  .awc a:hover{text-decoration:underline}
  .awc .crumb{font-size:12.5px; color:var(--ink-3); margin:0 0 16px}
  .awc .crumb a{color:var(--accent)}
  .awc h1{font-size:32px; line-height:1.18; font-weight:700; margin:0 0 12px; letter-spacing:-.01em; color:var(--indigo-deep); font-family:var(--serif)}
  .awc .lede{font-size:19px; color:var(--ink-2); margin:0 0 18px}
  .awc h2{font-size:21px; line-height:1.25; font-weight:700; margin:40px 0 14px; letter-spacing:-.01em; color:var(--indigo-deep); font-family:var(--serif)}
  .awc p{margin:0 0 16px}
  .awc strong{color:var(--ink)}

  /* question entries */
  .awc-item{background:#fff; border:1px solid var(--line); border-left:4px solid var(--accent); border-radius:0 12px 12px 0; padding:18px 22px; margin:0 0 16px}
  .awc-item h3{font-family:var(--serif); font-size:19px; color:var(--indigo-deep); margin:0 0 10px}
  .awc-item dl{margin:0}
  .awc-item dt{font-size:12px; letter-spacing:.04em; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--ink-3); font-weight:700; margin:10px 0 2px}
  .awc-item dd{margin:0; font-size:15.5px; color:var(--ink-2); line-height:1.6}
  .awc-status{display:inline-block; font-family:var(--sans); font-size:12px; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:.03em; color:var(--accent-deep); background:var(--accent-wash); border:1px solid var(--accent-soft); border-radius:999px; padding:2px 11px}
  .awc-empty{background:var(--paper-2); border:1px dashed var(--rule-strong); border-radius:12px; padding:16px 20px; color:var(--ink-3); font-size:15px}
  .awc-how{margin:0 0 14px; padding-left:22px}
  .awc-how li{margin:0 0 10px; line-height:1.6; color:var(--ink-2)}
  .awc-byline{font-size:14px; color:var(--ink-3); margin:34px 0 0; padding-top:16px; border-top:1px solid var(--rule)}
</style>
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
<div class="awc">
<div class="wrap">

  <p class="crumb"><a href="/communities">Communities</a> › <a href="/communities/sagamok">Sagamok Anishnawbek</a> › Questions awaiting an answer</p>

  <h1>Questions awaiting an answer</h1>
  <p class="lede">A growing record of questions members have put to Sagamok Chief and Council, and to the Nation's offices, that are still awaiting a reply. Each entry is tied to a public source or an as-filed document, framed as a question, not an accusation. We post the date asked and the status, and we update it as answers come in. Where there is no reply, that is recorded too. Silence is its own kind of answer.</p>

  {% set banner_body %}<strong>Member-compiled and unofficial.</strong> This is independent and member-led. It is not the Robinson Huron Treaty Litigation Fund and is not affiliated with it. It takes no side; it points to what the documents say. <a href="/about#corrections">Tell us what we got wrong</a> and we will correct it.{% endset %}
  {% include 'components/notice.html.twig' with { variant: 'caveat', body: banner_body, label: 'About this page' } only %}

  <h2>Open</h2>

  <div class="awc-item">
    <h3>Member records request (16 questions, plus a supplement)</h3>
    <dl>
      <dt>Asked</dt>
      <dd>June 10, 2026, to Chief and Council through the Council Secretariat.</dd>
      <dt>What it asks</dt>
      <dd>How the Nation's settlement capital and enterprise investments are governed and what benefit reaches members, the trust deed and who controls it, the loans to the Nation's companies and their terms, the Finance and Audit Committee's independence, committee memberships, the records-access process, and more. Carried 88 plus member and supporter signatures, with a 30-day response requested.</dd>
      <dt>Status</dt>
      <dd><span class="awc-status">Awaiting</span> &middot; Read the full request: <a href="/standard/records-request">the records request</a>.</dd>
    </dl>
  </div>

  <div class="awc-item">
    <h3>The July 20 Elders Forum and day trip</h3>
    <dl>
      <dt>Asked</dt>
      <dd>June 2026, to the Political Office.</dd>
      <dt>What it asks</dt>
      <dd>Which department owns and funds the event (catering, busing, and agenda) and why an elders program is administered through the Political Office rather than a wellness or service department; and what consideration was given to elder financial wellbeing in scheduling a stop at a casino on a band-organized, band-funded elders trip, weeks after settlement distributions, including who approved it and out of which budget.</dd>
      <dt>Status</dt>
      <dd><span class="awc-status">Awaiting</span></dd>
      <dt>Source</dt>
      <dd>The Nation's public notice for the Elders Forum, July 20, 2026.</dd>
    </dl>
  </div>

  <h2>Answered</h2>
  <p class="awc-empty">Nothing here yet. As replies arrive, they move to this section with the date and a short summary of what was provided.</p>

  <h2>How this list works</h2>
  <ul class="awc-how">
    <li>Every item is a question grounded in a public source or an as-filed document, never an accusation about any person.</li>
    <li>An item stays under "Open" until the Nation provides a written answer, then it moves to "Answered" with the date and what was said.</li>
    <li>This is a member resource. If you have asked Council something and are still waiting, or if you think we have a detail wrong, <a href="/about#corrections">tell the Circle</a> and we will record it or correct it.</li>
  </ul>

  <p class="awc-byline">A community resource from the Robinson Huron Treaty hub, member-led and independent. Facts are from public sources; the questions are for our leadership. Corrections welcome.</p>

</div>
</div>
{% endblock %}
